    <text type="letter">
        <body> 
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1890-09-20">PM Sept: 20 '90</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Best remembrance &#38; love to all&#8212;I am getting along better than you w'd
                suppose (have this tenacious grip though)&#8212;was out last Sunday&#8212;was
                propell'd in the wheel chair<ptr target="loc.03012_n1"/>&#8212;to my Camden friends Mr. and Mrs. T B Harned<ptr
                    target="n4146"/><ptr target="n4134"/> who treated me to a splendid meal of oysters &#38;
                champagne&#8212;to wh' <hi rend="italic">abstemious me</hi> did fullest justice (I
                think the best ch: I ever drank)&#8212;I am writing a little annex (the 2d) to L of
                G.<ptr target="loc.07894_n2"/> &#38; giving out the design of my burial vault
                (on a little wooded slope in Harleigh Cemetery<ptr target="loc.07329_n5"/> here)&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>the Lord bless you all&#8212;</salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Give this to Alma<ptr target="n3029"/> &#38; the girls<ptr target="loc.07838_n2"/>&#8212;</p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
    </text> 
